Several MCP server implementations exist to integrate Twenty CRM with AI assistants like Claude, enabling natural language CRUD operations and schema management [1][2][3]. Most implementations, such as those by mhenry3164 or studio7A, provide standard tools for contacts, companies, tasks, and notes [3][4]. If you are using a self-hosted version of Twenty CRM (specifically v1.19.0), you should use the fork maintained by Praeses0, which addresses specific GraphQL API incompatibilities like UUID requirements and body field changes [2].

To configure an MCP server, add it to your configuration file:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "twenty-crm": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/server/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "TWENTY_API_KEY": "your_api_key_here",
        "TWENTY_BASE_URL": "https://api.twenty.com"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Most versions require your API key and base URL as environment variables [3][5].
